Question 4

phone_strings <- c("Home: (507)-645-5489", 
                   "Cell: 219.917.9871", 
                   "My work phone is 507-202-2332",
                   "I don't have a phone")
substrings <- str_subset(phone_strings, "\\d{3}[-.]")
substrings2 <- str_replace_all(substrings, pattern = "[:alpha:]", "")
substrings3 <- str_replace_all(substrings2, pattern = ":", "")
substrings4 <- str_replace_all(substrings3, pattern = "\\(", "")
substrings5 <- str_replace_all(substrings4, pattern = "\\)", "")
substrings6 <- str_replace_all(substrings5, pattern = "\\.", " ")
substrings7 <- str_trim(substrings6)
substrings8 <- str_replace_all(substrings7, pattern = " ", "-")
substrings8
## [1] "507-645-5489" "219-917-9871" "507-202-2332"

Question 6

s <- c("1one", "22two", "333three", "4444four")

# Find
str_subset(s, pattern = "\\d{2}")
## [1] "22two"    "333three" "4444four"
str_view(s, pattern = "\\d{2}")
## [2] │ <22>two
## [3] │ <33>3three
## [4] │ <44><44>four
# The subset returns the last three vectors because they all contain numbers that are at least two digits.
str_subset(s, "^\\d{2}[:alpha:]")
## [1] "22two"
str_view(s, "^\\d{2}[:alpha:]")
## [2] │ <22t>wo

Question 3

long_square <- function(x) {
  len <- length(x)
  sqrtofsum <- sqrt(sum(x))
  if (len>sqrtofsum) {
    print("long!")
  } else {
    print("not long!")
  }
}
x1 <- c(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)
x2 <- c(5, 8, 10, 12)
x3 <- c(2, 5, 9, 10, 1, 1, 1)
long_square(x = x1)
## [1] "long!"
long_square(x = x2)
## [1] "not long!"
long_square(x = x3)
## [1] "long!"

Question 4

top_table <- function(z, n, top) {ss <- table(z)
sortState <- sort(ss, decreasing = top)
  print(head(sortState,n))
}
top_table(police$state, n = 5, top = TRUE)
## z
##  CA  TX  FL  AZ  CO 
## 825 496 369 259 204
top_table(college$State, n = 10, top = FALSE)
## z
## GU VI WY AK DE HI NV ID NM ND 
##  1  1  1  2  5  6  6  7  7  8

Question 5

List1 <- list.files(pattern = "csv")

mean_vec <- numeric(length = length(List1))
expergroup <- character(length = length(List1))
gender <- character(length = length(List1))
for (i in seq_along(mean_vec)) {
  dat <- read.csv(List1[i])
  mean_vec[i] <- mean(dat$x)
  newList <- str_replace(List1[i], pattern = ".csv", "")
  
  expergroup[i] <- str_extract(newList, pattern = ".$")
  newList1 <- str_replace(newList, pattern = "exp.$", "")
  gender[i] <- str_extract(newList1, pattern = ".$")
  
}

table1 <- data.frame(M = mean_vec, Exp = expergroup, sex = gender)
ggplot(table1, aes(M, sex, fill = sex)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  facet_wrap(~Exp) +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(x = "Value", y = "Sex")

Question 3

# Part A & B
marathon <- read.csv("https://remiller1450.github.io/data/BostonMarathon2015.csv")
library(dplyr)
mara2 <- marathon %>%
  mutate(half1 = hms(Half) %>% seconds()) %>%
  mutate(ppm1 = (half1/13.1)) %>%
  mutate(ppm2 = (hms(Official.Time) - hms(Half))/13.1 %>% seconds())

library(ggplot2)
# Part C
ggplot(mara2, aes(ppm1, ppm2, color = Age)) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.2) +
  facet_wrap(~M.F) +
  scale_color_continuous(type = "gradient") +
  geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0, linetype = "dashed") +
  labs(x = "First Half Pace per Mile", y = "Second Half Pace per Mile") +
  scale_x_time() +
  scale_y_time() + theme_bw()
